One fan put the angst of Manchester City's crumbling Champions League campaign to the back of his mind at the Etihad on Wednesday night as he made himself a sandwich in the stands.

Amazingly the supporter took out a whole loaf of bread and a jar of peanut butter and was pictured making the 'sarnie' in his front-row seat at arguably City's biggest match of the season.

Manuel Pellegrini's side's Champions League hopes were left hanging by a thread after they were beaten 2-1 at home by Russian outfit CSKA Moscow, and unlike most supporters, this fan will have left the stadium fairly satisfied after his mid-match snack.

