Perhaps even more inexplicable is the fact that the fan must have pre-planned his late lunch after turning up to the match with the loaf of bread, the peanut butter and presumably a utensil for spreading the filling.

Support at the Etihad during Manchester City's campaign in Europe's top club competition has come in for criticism this season, and this supporter's snack-making antics will not have helped the situation.

A first-half brace by CSKA's Seydou Doumbia was enough to seal the win for the Moscow club despite Yaya Toure's equaliser as Man City were left staring elimination in the face.

